SIMPLE: zealous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zealous
<hw>Zeal"ous</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>zelosus</ets>. See <er>Zeal</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Filled with, or characterized by, zeal; warmly
engaged, or ardent, in behalf of an object.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He may be <qex>zealous</qex> in the salvation of souls.</q>
<rj><qau>Law.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Filled with religious zeal.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Zeal"ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Zeal"ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zebec</ent>⟦br⟧
